en_182693_0	The Indian Government has increased its budget allocations for its neighbours including Sri Lanka to counter the rising Chinese dominance in the region.
en_182693_1	Other nations to receive increased benefits under the new measures are Seychelles, Mauritius and the Maldives.
en_182693_2	Accordingly, India has planned to provide financial aid of 150 Indian Crores to Sri Lanka.
en_182693_3	This is double the funds received by Sri Lanka compared to last year.
en_182693_4	India has expressed a special desire to renovate Kankesanthurai Port this year.
